C-dots(1 mL), NR (160 μL), HCl (100 μL) and reaction time (10 min) were selected as the optimal reaction parameters (Fig. S3). One milliliter of C-dots had strong fluorescent emission (Fig. S3a) and their fluorescent emission was almost quenched by adding 160 μL of NR (Fig. S3b). The ratio of fluorescent intensity (F/F0) reached the maximum at pH value of 1.2 indicating that the reaction was the fastest (Fig. S3c). The fluorescence ratio (F/F

